objecttypes.name: Information
objecttypes.title: Information product
objecttypes.description: Represent the product to be generated.

properties.name: VerticalMeasurements
properties.description: Depths and elevations pertaining to the well, like, water depth, mud line elevation, etc.

properties.name: InterestType
properties.description: Pre-defined reasons for interest in the well or information about the well.

properties.name: AccessControlLIst
properties.description: The access control tags associated with this entity. This structure is included by the SystemProperties \"acl\", which is part of all OSDU records. Not extensible.

properties.name: WellboreTrajectoryType
properties.description: Describes the predominant shapes the wellbore path can follow if deviated from vertical. Sample Values: Horizontal, Vertical, Directional.

properties.name: ancestry
properties.description: The links to data, which constitute the inputs.

properties.name: meta
properties.description: The Frame of Reference meta data section linking the named properties to self-contained definitions.

properties.name: TrajectoryType
properties.description: Describes the predominant shapes the wellbore path can follow if deviated from vertical. Sample Values: Horizontal, Vertical, Directional.

properties.name: ProjectedLocation
properties.description: The bottom hole location of the wellbore denoted by a projected horizontal coordinate reference system (Horizontal CRS), such a UTM zone. 'Projected' in this property does not mean 'planned' or 'projected-to-bit'. If both GeographicBottomHoleLocation and ProjectedBottomHoleLocation properties are populated on this wellbore, they must identify the same point, just in different CRSs.

properties.name: GeographicLocation
properties.description: The Formation of interest for which the Wellbore is drilled to interact with. The Wellbore may terminate in a lower formation if the requirement is to drill through the entirety of the target formation, therefore this is not necessarily the Formation at TD.

properties.name: TopDepthMeasuredDepth
properties.description: Measured depth in wellbore where the directional survey starts. This should equal the minimum station measured depth for this directional survey, regardless of whether the surveyed station represents an actual surveyed MD or not.

properties.name: ActiveIndicator
properties.description: A flag indicating if the survey is currently active or valid within his lifecycle stage, not necessarily the definitive survey.

properties.name: SurveyType
properties.description: The type of this directional survey.  For example a \"Directional Survey\" where MD, Inclination and Azimuth are all measured or a \"Position Log\" where Inclination and Azimuth are both null and only MD, TVD and X/Y Offsets are available) - or \"Full Survey\" where everything is fully filled-up, depth-inclination-azimuth.

properties.name: AcquisitionDate
properties.description: The date that the survey data was acquired on the field.

properties.name: AcquisitionRemark
properties.description: Remarks related to acquisition context which is not the same as Description which is a summary of the work-product-component.

properties.name: SurveyReferenceIdentifier
properties.description: Unique or Distinctive Survey Reference Number, Job Number, File Number, Identifier, Label, Name, etc. as indicated on a directional survey report, file, etc.  Use this attribute to allow correlation of the data in this Directional Survey back to the original source document, file, etc.

properties.name: SurveyToolTypeID
properties.description: The type of tool or equipment used to acquire this Directional Survey.  For example, gyroscopic, magnetic, MWD, TOTCO, acid bottle, etc. Follow OWSG reference data and support the ISCWSA survey tool definitions.

properties.name: SurveyVersion
properties.description: The version of the wellbore survey deliverable received from the service provider - as given by this provider

properties.name: ExtrapolatedMeasuredDepth
properties.description: The measured depth to which the survey segment was extrapolated.

properties.name: BaseDepthMeasuredDepth
properties.description: Measured depth within the wellbore of the LAST surveyed station with recorded data.  If a stored survey has been extrapolated to a deeper depth than the last surveyed station then that is the extrapolated measured depth and not the survey base depth.

properties.name: TieMeasuredDepth
properties.description: Tie-point depth measured along the wellbore from the measurement reference datum to the survey station - where tie point is the place on the originating survey where the current survey intersect it.

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all survey station measured depths.

properties.name: MarkerName
properties.description: Name of the Marker

properties.name: MarkerMeasuredDepth
properties.description: The depth at which the Marker was noted.

properties.name: MarkerDate
properties.description: Timestamp of the date and time when the when the Marker was interpreted.

properties.name: MarkerObservationNumber
properties.description: Any observation number that distinguishes a Marker observation from others with same Marker name, date.

properties.name: MarkerInterpreter
properties.description: The name of the Marker interpreter (could be a person or vendor).

properties.name: FeatureName
properties.description: Name of the feature the marker is characterizing.

properties.name: PositiveVerticalDelta
properties.description: The distance vertically above the Marker position that marks the limit of the high confidence range for the Marker pick.

properties.name: NegativeVerticalDelta
properties.description: The distance vertically below the Marker position that marks the limit of the high confidence range for the Marker pick.

properties.name: SurfaceDipAngle
properties.description: Dip angle for the Wellbore Marker.

properties.name: SurfaceDipAzimuth
properties.description: Dip azimuth for the Wellbore Marker.

datatypes.name: Coordinate
datatypes.description: The default vertical coordinate reference system used in the vertical measurements for a well or wellbore if absent from input vertical measurements and there is no other recourse for obtaining a valid CRS.

datatypes.name: Entity ID
datatypes.description: Previously called ResourceID or SRN which identifies this OSDU resource object without version.

datatypes.name: Entity Kind
datatypes.description: The schema identification for the OSDU resource object following the pattern {Namespace}:{Source}:{Type}:{VersionMajor}.{VersionMinor}.{VersionPatch}. The versioning scheme follows the semantic versioning, https://semver.org/.

datatypes.name: PointId
datatypes.description: The default datum reference point, or zero depth point, used to determine other points vertically in a well.  References an entry in the VerticalMeasurements array.

datatypes.name: Resource Object Creation DateTime
datatypes.description: Timestamp of the time at which initial version of this OSDU resource object was created. Set by the System. The value is a combined date-time string in ISO-8601 given in UTC.

datatypes.name: Resource Object Creation User Reference
datatypes.description: The user reference, which created the first version of this resource object. Set by the System.

datatypes.name: Resource Object Version Creation DateTime
